# Assignment 2 — Data Structures in Java

Custom implementations of ArrayList, LinkedList, Stack, Queue, and MinHeap without java.util.* (except Iterator).

## Files
MyList.java | Interface for all list implementations
MyArrayList.java | Dynamic array-backed list 
MyLinkedList.java | Doubly linked list 
MyStack.java | LIFO stack — backed by MyArrayList
MyQueue.java | FIFO queue — backed by MyLinkedList
MyMinHeap.java | Min-heap — backed by MyArrayList

## Design Choices
- Stack uses MyArrayList — O(1) access to last element for push/pop
- Queue uses MyLinkedList — O(1) insert at tail and remove from head
- MinHeap uses MyArrayList — index arithmetic maps naturally to parent/child nodes
